               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184201030150"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420103-name-996" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420103-name-996" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420103-name-996" type="surname" value="WADE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420103-name-996" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
GEORGE WADE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a grocer, and live in High-street, Deptford—the prisoner was my shopman. On the 11th of December I told him I had reason to suspect he was robbing me, and asked if he had any objection to be searched—he said "No"—I asked if he had any objection to have his box looked into—he said "No"—he then went up stairs with me and the policeman—I saw him give the policeman the key—the policeman opened his box, and found in it this tobacco, these cigars, and this pencil<lb></lb>case—I know they are mine, as I had taken the precaution that morning to sprinkle a little green tea in my tobacco, and this tobacco has the tea in it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420103-name-997" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420103-name-997" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420103-name-997" type="surname" value="LOVELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420103-name-997" type="given" value="BENJAMIN"></interp>BENJAMIN LOVELL</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-sergeant R</hi> 15.) I went with Mr. Wade, and opened the box—I found these things—I saw the tea in the tobacco—it was shown to the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I took a quarter of a pound of tobacco from the stock, and put a shilling into the till for it; the cigars were unsaleable, and put on one side—the pencil-case was in the dust-hole.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. WADE</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> It might be about the yard, as my children played with it—the cigars were not unsaleable at that time—he said he had had the tobacco ever since he had been in my employment.</p>
               <p>
